## Tabs

- **Report** tab â€” upload/folder, preflight, generate, appendices, downloads.
- **AI tools** tab â€” optional narrative/source ingest (`ui/ai_panel.py`); drafts do not auto-merge into render unless copied to Excel or sidebar override.

## Batch mode

When batch mode and `ProjectData` has more than one data row, `app.py` offers **Single report** vs **All N reports (batch)**. Batch calls **`render_service.render_batch_reports()`** and stores results in `session_state.generated_batch` for `render_batch_download_section`. Same uploaded appendices apply to every row.

## UX rules

- On launch, users **choose a workflow** (`ui/workflow_mode.py`): project folder + AI or Excel + template upload.
- Persist **generated bytes and manifest** in **session state** so download survives reruns.
- **Widget session keys** â€” never assign `st.session_state.<widget_key>` after that widget is drawn (Streamlit raises `StreamlitAPIException`). Set pending values before the widget (e.g. `project_folder_path_pending` â†’ assign `project_folder_path_input` at top of `_render_folder_controls`).
- Surface **user-safe** errors from `security.user_safe_error`; do not leak raw tracebacks for uploads.
- Preflight cache key includes appendix label tuple â€” changing uploads invalidates preflight; engine cache also keys on appendix + ecoventure digest.
